{ Markdown Grammar for iXML

  Purpose: Parse Markdown documentation preserving semantic structure
  Output: XML with heading hierarchy, code blocks, lists, links

  Key Features:
  - Preserves heading hierarchy (h1-h6)
  - Extracts code blocks with language tags
  - Captures lists (ordered, unordered)
  - Preserves links and inline code

  Example Input:
    # API Documentation

    ## Authentication

    Use the `Authorization` header:

    ```javascript
    fetch('/api', { headers: { 'Authorization': 'Bearer token' } })
    ```

  Example Output:
    <markdown>
      <h1>API Documentation</h1>
      <h2>Authentication</h2>
      <paragraph>Use the <code>Authorization</code> header:</paragraph>
      <code-block lang="javascript">fetch('/api', { headers: { 'Authorization': 'Bearer token' } })</code-block>
    </markdown>
}

markdown: content* .

content: heading | code-block | list | paragraph | blank-line .

{ Headings (h1-h6) }
heading: h1 | h2 | h3 | h4 | h5 | h6 .
h1: -'# ', text, line-ending .
h2: -'## ', text, line-ending .
h3: -'### ', text, line-ending .
h4: -'#### ', text, line-ending .
h5: -'##### ', text, line-ending .
h6: -'###### ', text, line-ending .

{ Code blocks with language tag }
code-block: code-block-with-lang | code-block-plain .
code-block-with-lang: -'```', @lang: identifier, line-ending, code-content, -'```', line-ending .
code-block-plain: -'```', line-ending, code-content, -'```', line-ending .
code-content: code-line* .
code-line: ~['`'], line-ending .

{ Lists }
list: unordered-list | ordered-list .
unordered-list: list-item-ul+ .
ordered-list: list-item-ol+ .
list-item-ul: -['*'; '-'; '+'], -' ', inline-text, line-ending .
list-item-ol: digit+, -'. ', inline-text, line-ending .

{ Paragraphs with inline formatting }
paragraph: inline-text, line-ending .
inline-text: (inline-code | link | bold | italic | plain-text)+ .

inline-code: -'`', text, -'`' .
link: -'[', @text: link-text, -']', -'(', @url: link-url, -')' .
link-text: (~[']'])+ .
link-url: (~[')'])+ .
bold: -'**', text, -'**' .
italic: -'*', text, -'*' .

{ Basic text and primitives }
plain-text: (~['`'; '['; '*'; #a])+ .
text: (~[#a])+ .
identifier: ['a'-'z'; 'A'-'Z'; '0'-'9'; '-'; '_']+ .
digit: ['0'-'9'] .

{ Line handling }
blank-line: -#a .
line-ending: -#a .
